1. **Precision**: Each bounding box should perfectly enclose one single target object. In this image, each bounding box does enclose a single tower crane, even though some parts of the cranes are occluded by the buildings. The bounding boxes are reasonably estimated based on the visible parts of the cranes.
2. **Recall**: All target objects should be localized by a bounding box. In this image, there are three tower cranes, and all three are annotated with bounding boxes.
3. **Fit**: Each bounding box should neither be too loose nor too tight. The bounding boxes in this image are well-fitted to the tower cranes, with slight allowances for occlusion and reasonable estimations of the cranes' sizes.
